{
  "texts": [
    "In the rapidly evolving landscape of digital transformation, enterprise organizations are seeking intelligent solutions to optimize internal operations, improve customer support, and automate knowledge access.",
    "Traditional rule-based chatbots, while effective for scripted responses, often lack the adaptability and contextual understanding required for dynamic, domain-specific queries.",
    "These limitations have driven the adoption of more sophisticated natural language processing (NLP) technologies, particularly those based on transformer architectures.",
    "Recent advancements, such as OpenAI's GPT-3.5, have demonstrated remarkable language generation capabilities when applied to generalized conversational tasks [1].",
    "However, their standalone use in enterprise environments is limited due to their dependency on training data and inability to recall proprietary or task-specific knowledge."
  ]
}